The paper deals with the achievable rate of a communication channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The use of power spectral density (PSD) and the assumption of compactly supported PSD are common in signal processing (cs.SI) and networking (cs.NI). The paper also involves the derivation of upper bounds and pre-logs, which are techniques used in mathematical analysis (cs.MA).
